-- Turkey's Sabanci Holding Q2 net profit rises 4.5 percent 
-- 
-- Fri Aug 15, 2014 10:58AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 15 (Reuters) - Turkey's Sabanci Holding <SAHOL.IS> posted a 4.5 percent rise in second quarter net profit to 558.8 million lira ($257.24 million), it said in a filing on Friday.

The conglomerate's sales rose 29 percent on the year to 7.1 billion lira, its results posted on Istanbul stock exchange showed.